BYU RapidSmith Tools 0.4.0

Packages
edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.bitstreamTools.bitstream This package is used to represent a Xilinx FPGA bitstream file.
edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.bitstreamTools.bitstream.test This package contains several test scripts and classes aimed at testing the functionality of the bitstream package.
edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.bitstreamTools.configuration This package emulates an FPGA that can be configured with the Bitstream class and can also be read back to create bitstreams.
edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.bitstreamTools.configurationSpecification This package specifies the bitstream details of the architectures supported and contains classes to automatically generate new part libraries.
edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.bitstreamTools.examples This package contains several examples of how to use the bitstream tools contained in RapidSmith.
edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.bitstreamTools.examples.support This package contains some supporting classes for the examples given in the bitstream tools in RapidSmith.
edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.design The design package has all the classes necessary to represent XDL designs in RapidSmith.
edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.design.explorer This package contains the main classes to run the Design Explorer tool in RapidSmith.
edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.design.parser The design.parser package is a parser for XDL and populates the classes found in the design package.
edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.device The device package represents all of the resources available on an FPGA device (part name, tiles, primitive sites and routing resources).
edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.device.browser This package contains the main classes to run the Device Browser tool in RapidSmith.
edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.device.helper The device.helper package is a set of classes which are used for creating and populating the Device class and other classes in the device package.
edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.examples The examples package is a set of classes which are examples to illustrate how to use RapidSmith.
edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.gui The gui package contains classes that can aid in graphical tool development in RapidSmith.
edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.placer The placer package will have a full design placer, but it is still under construction at the moment.
edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.primitiveDefs The primitiveDefs package is a set of classes which describe and represent the primitive definitions found at the end of XDLRC report files.
edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.router This package contains a basic router and structure to help users build routers of their own.
edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.tests This package contains classes to help test and maintain RapidSmith.
edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.timing This package contains all classes relating to timing information produced by Xilinx Trace (trce).
edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.util The util package contains several classes aimed at helping RapidSmith users do a variety of operations such as install RapidSmith, convert files, and run certain Xilinx tools from within RapidSmith.
